    "context_preserved": "The unified IfxEgtm_Pwm driver is used to configure EGTM Cluster_1 ATOM0 CH0/1/2 for 20 kHz center-aligned PWM with complementary DTM outputs and 1 µs dead-time. SyncStart is achieved with IfxEgtm_Pwm_startSyncedChannels; syncUpdate is honored by using the unified driver's synchronized update paths, while independent phase duty updates are performed via IfxEgtm_Pwm_updateChannelDutyImmediate. FXCLK_0 and CLK0 are enabled via IfxEgtm_Cmu/IfxEgtm_Dtm APIs. A period ISR on CPU0 (prio 20) invokes IfxEgtm_Pwm_interruptHandler and toggles LED P13.0 using IfxPort. Pin mapping uses IfxEgtm_PinMap for the specified P20.x TOUTs; verify exact P20.x TOUT macros in IfxEgtm_PinMap.h for KIT_A3G_TC4D7_LITE."
  },
